cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of co-training and correlation filters, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with multi-feature templates, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis and retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed method, which is a common concern in robotics and control systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
